xyz.swatt.selenium

Class WebElementWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • xyz.swatt.selenium.WebElementWrapper
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    WebElementTransitionalWrapper 

    public class WebElementWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is a wrapper for the Selenium WebElement class.

    It's purpose is to make common tasks easier and catch/fix common problems.

    All WebDriver interactions are Synchronized on the WebDriverWrapper.LOCK object. (The WebDriver / Web Browser can only do one thing at a time, just like a real person.) This allows Multi-Threading to be used with Selenium.

    Author:
    Brandon Dudek (BrandonDudek)

      • click

        public WebElementWrapper click()
        Hovers over the WebElement, then clicks it.

        Note: If the WebElement is not visible in the browser's viewport, it will be scrolled to the middle of the viewport.

        Same as calling click(boolean) with a value of false.

        Known Issues: Some WebElements do not work with Selenium's built-in click() function. In those cases, use javascriptClick().

        Known WebElements that need a Javascript Click:

        - Bootstrap's Date-Time Picker Widget

        Returns:
        This WebElementWrapper for function call chain-ability.
        Throws:
        org.openqa.selenium.WebDriverException - If the WebElement is covered, and another WebElement would receive the click.

        public WebElementWrapper click(double _waitTimeInSeconds,
                               boolean _waitForRefresh)
        Waits for this WebElement to be click-able, hovers over it, clicks it, and optionally waits for a page refresh.

        Note: If the WebElement is not visible in the browser's viewport, it will be scrolled to the middle of the viewport.

        Known Issues: Some WebElements do not work with Selenium's built-in click() function. In those cases, use javascriptClick().

        Known WebElements that need a Javascript Click:

        - Bootstrap's Date-Time Picker Widget

        _waitTimeInSeconds - The Maximum amount of time to wait for this WebElement to be click-able (truncated to a long).

        This WebElementWrapper for function call chain-ability.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If _waitTimeInSeconds < 0.
        org.openqa.selenium.TimeoutException - If this WebElement is not click-able after _waitTimeInSeconds.

        Or if the page never unloads, or if the page does not finish loading in WebDriverWrapper.maxPageLoadTime seconds.

        See Also:

      • getDescendant

        public WebElementWrapper getDescendant(org.openqa.selenium.By _by)
        Waits WebDriverWrapper.maxElementLoadTime for a descendant WebElement, that match the given search query, to exist and contain the correct visibility; then grabs that WebElement descendants.
        Parameters:
        _by - How to search for the descendant.

        If looking for a direct decedent, do NOT start with the CSS "child combinator" selector (>). This CSS selector MUST be preceded by a parent query.Instead use an XPath starting with "./".

        Note: XPaths starting with "//" will be updated to start with ".//".

        Returns:
        A WebElementWrapper that is a descendants of this Element and matches the given search query and visibility; or null, if no such descendant was found.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the given By object is null.

        Or if the given By object is a CSS Selector starts with ">".

        org.openqa.selenium.NoSuchElementException - If no Web Element is found, and the _notFoundError argument is not null.
        TooManyResultsException - If more than one descendant is found.

      • getValue

        public java.lang.String getValue()
        Will return the value of this WebElement regardless of the type.
        • Input Element: "value" Attribute
        • Text Area Element: "value" Attribute
        • Select Element:
          • If no option(s) are selected, null is returned.
          • If only 1 option is selected, the value of the selected option is returned.
          • If multiple options are selected, a JSON representation of the selected options in list format is returned. (Note: use getSelectOptionsSelected() to get all values in List format.)
        • Links (Anchor Tags): Visible Text
        • Regular Dom Element: Visible Text

        Note: If returning the Visible Text, the Element will be scrolled to first.

        Returns:
        The value of this WebElement.

      • javascriptClick

        public WebElementWrapper javascriptClick()
        Hovers over this WebElement and clicks it using JavaScript.

        (This is helpful for WebElements that do not work with Selenium's built-in WebElement.click() function.)

        Known WebElements that need a JavaScript click:

        - Bootstrap's Date-Time Picker Widget

        Note: If the WebElement is not visible in the viewport, it will be scrolled to the middle of the viewport.

        Known Issues: Some WebElements do not work with a JavaScript click. For those Elements use the normal click() function.

        Known WebElements:

        - Summernote

        Returns:
        This WebElementWrapper for function call chain-ability.
        Throws:
        org.openqa.selenium.WebDriverException - If the WebElement is covered, and another WebElement would receive the click.

        public void rightClick()

        • To navigate through the Context Menu items, send Keys.UP and Keys.DOWN to this element.
        • To select/execute/perform a highlighted Context Menu item, send Keys.ENTER to this element.

        Waits up to WebDriverWrapper.maxElementLoadTime, for this Element's value to equal a given value.

        Note: Both the actual value and the given value are trimmed before comparing.

        Parameters:
        _value - The value to compare against.
        _caseSensitive - If true, String.equals(Object) is used; else if false, String.equalsIgnoreCase(String) is used.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the given Value is null.
        org.openqa.selenium.TimeoutException - If this Web Element's Value does not change in the given amount of time.

      • waitForValue

        public void waitForValue(java.lang.String _value,
                         java.time.Duration _waitTime,
                         boolean _caseSensitive,
                         boolean _isEqualTo)
        Waits up to the given length of time, for this Element's value to equal / not equal a given value.

        Note: Both the actual value and the given value are trimmed before comparing.

        Parameters:
        _value - The value to compare against.
        _waitTime - How long to wait for the change to occur.
        _caseSensitive - If true, String.equals(Object) is used; else if false, String.equalsIgnoreCase(String) is used.
        _isEqualTo - If true, waits for the value to equal the given value; else if false, waits for the value to not equal the given value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the given Value is null.

        Or if the given Wait Time is < 0.

        org.openqa.selenium.TimeoutException - If this Web Element's Value does not change in the given amount of time.

      • waitForVisibility

        public void waitForVisibility()
        Waits up to WebDriverWrapper.maxElementLoadTime, for this Web Element to become visible.

        Note: If waiting for Invisibility, a Stale Element will be treated as Invisible.

        Throws:
        org.openqa.selenium.TimeoutException - If this Web Element's Visibility does not change in the given amount of time.

      • waitForVisibility

        public void waitForVisibility(boolean _visible)
        Waits up to WebDriverWrapper.maxElementLoadTime, for this Web Element to become visible/invisible.

        Note: If waiting for Invisibility, a Stale Element will be treated as Invisible.

        Parameters:
        _visible - True if we are waiting for Web Element to be visible, or false if we are waiting for Web Element to be invisible.
        Throws:
        org.openqa.selenium.TimeoutException - If this Web Element's Visibility does not change in the given amount of time.

      • waitForVisibility

        Waits up to the given length of time, for this Web Element to become visible.
        Parameters:

        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the given Wait Time is negative.
        org.openqa.selenium.TimeoutException - If this Web Element's Visibility does not change in the given amount of time.
